headline: McKesson Stock Shoots To Record High. Health Products Giant Shows Improved Price Strength
summary: Health care products giant McKesson's stock broke out of a flat base Tuesday and jumped to a record high.  Last quarter Irving, Texas-based McKesson reported a 5% earnings gain to $8.26 per share on a 23% surge in revenue to $97.8 billion.  Meanwhile, the Relative Strength (RS) Rating for McKesson stock climbed into a higher percentile as it got a lift from 66 to 79 Wednesday.

headline: McKesson (MCK) Stock Is Up, What You Need To Know
summary: Shares of healthcare distributor and services company McKesson (NYSE:MCK) jumped 2.6% in the morning session after the positive momentum continued as it raised its profit forecast for fiscal 2026 and boosted its long-term growth targets during its 2025 Investor Day.
